        "client_msg_id": "da96a018-4ce9-403f-824f-0ead82c27db6",
        "text": "Following some prolog tutorials, it looks like the data\/terms always has sort of a \"global scope\".\n\nHow do ppl manage the \"database\" on medium \/ big prolog programs?\nCan there be more than one database?\nAre there some sort of namespacing and\/or modularity features?\n\nSometimes the concept of relations is a bit mind-boggling because it seems difficult to distinguish between relations that act as \"routines\" or \"procedures\", or something alike, and terms that act more like pure data.\nIt just feels like, if I was writing an imperative program in prolog style, it would be something akin to code interspersed with, say, embedded CSV data :confused:\nHope this makes a bit of sense :slightly_smiling_face:",
